"created_at":"2022-03-18T15:23:14Z","updated_at":"2022-04-23T22:40:56Z","closed_at":"2022-04-23T22:40:56Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"**Link to fork with a repro in the issue-repro module**\r\nhttps://github.com/dekalo-stanislav/lottie-android/pull/1\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nLottieView progress field value could be greater than setMaxProgress(`value`).\r\n\r\n**Use case:**\r\nWe are trying to use LottieView as a progress view, where we can animate between progress states.\r\nWe use setMaxProgress(`value`) and playAnimation() to display current progress.\r\nHowever sometimes LottieView displays wrong progress. (Greater than `value` used in `setMaxProgress`)\r\n\r\n**Issue details**\r\nIt looks like when we call `setMaxProgress` on `LottieAnimationView` with some particular value.\r\n`LottieAnimationView` do not fully respect `setMaxProgress` value and actual `progress` of the view might get greater than max value previously set.\r\n\r\n**Steps To Reproduce**\r\n\r\n1. Run the issue IssueReproActivity activity\r\n2. No loop, no autoplay\r\n3. setMaxProgress(value) to 0.32f (just as an example)\r\n4. Start animation with playAnimation()\r\n5. Wait till animation end\r\n6. Compare progress value with 0.32f\r\nActual Result: progress is  0.32752827 that is greater than 0.32\r\nExpected Result: progress is <= 0.32\r\n\r\nSee details in the PR at the top.","closed_by":{"login":"gpeal","id":1307745,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzMDc3NDU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1307745?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/gpeal","html_url":"https://github.com/gpeal","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gpeal/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gpeal/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.git